                    <votes>0</votes>
                        <watches>0</watches>
                                                    <comments>
                    <comment id="12556024" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2008 19:08:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed only StandardAnalyzer to skip terms longer than 255 chars by&lt;br/&gt;
default (it turns out SimpleAnalyzer, WhitespaceAnalyzer, StopAnalyzer&lt;br/&gt;
already prune tokens at 255 chars).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can change the max allowed token length by calling&lt;br/&gt;
StandardAnalyzer.setMaxTokenLength.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t use LengthFilter, because 1) I wanted to avoid copying the&lt;br/&gt;
massive term only to then filter it (makes performance faster) and, 2)&lt;br/&gt;
I wanted to increment position increment for the next valid token&lt;br/&gt;
after a series of too-long tokens.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All tests pass.  I plan to commit in a day or two.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
